	<tr>
		
			<td colspan="2" bgcolor="#DEDACB" background="http://www.everlore.com/gimages/tb_beige.gif">
		
				<font face="verdana" size="2" color="black">
				Be very careful where you cast this if you are a mage.  The bind point is literally where you stand.  I made the mistake of binding to the lobby at Befallen.  Then, when I was ready to leave, I gated there.  Three big skeletons waxed me in a few blows.  Then... viola, I popped back to life next to those three skeletons only to be killed... then... AGAIN!  Ouch.  Lost some bubbles there.  I had to go link dead as quickly as possible hope someone came to clear the creatures.<BR>
<BR>
I find that casting this in fringe areas is best, like up a hill or such.  Or, even better, immediately adjacent to a zone point.<BR>
<BR>
You cannot bind others to anything other than a city ZONE.  And, anywhere in that zone (with exceptions like Faydark) will do.  For example, in east Freeport, just cast bind on the person anywhere.  They will show up at the same point as all other people... just outside the gate.  And... be sure to get your platinum piece ahead of time (my normal fee for bind) ;-)
				</font>
			</td>

	</tr>
	
