	<tr>
		
			<td colspan="2" bgcolor="#DEDACB" background="http://www.everlore.com/gimages/tb_beige.gif">
		
				<font face="verdana" size="2" color="black">
				A WORD OF WARNING<BR>
Yes it's true that if you die in the Same zone that you are bound in that your pet won't die!!<BR>
BUT BEWARE:<BR>
Make sure before you GATE, that your pet will actually DIE from the problem your gating from.<BR>
Why? you ask<BR>
I apparently got nervous and thought I was going to lose, so I gated. My pet was actually victorious, or was at least doing well long enough for about 3 more mobs to jump in on the fight! So, after he eventually DID die, guess what.. I had a self produced train slam down on me while I was meditating to recharge mana!!<BR>
 You see, whatever is fighting your pet, WILL come for you as soon as pet dies!!<BR>
  On the same token, I don't think it would be a good idea to Gate in this case even if NOT in a fight, like to just save time travelling across zone.. your pet in it's travels to re-join you, could pick up a few attackers. If he dies again, they will come for you!<BR>
 Wether you like it or not, I found that binding in a safe place, be it just the other side of the zone.. and staying there a while before returning is the safest bet. Because pet or no pet, if you gated to escape a problem, that problem will still come back and find you if you are still in the same zone!! At least bind at the zone, so if need be you can zone fast if there IS a problem!
				</font>
			</td>

	</tr>
	
